The only connected graph satisfying the given conditions is the cube graph (Q3) on 8 vertices. The number of labeled graphs isomorphic to the cube is given by \(8! / |\text{Aut}(Q3)| = 40320 / 48 = 840\). Thus, \(N = 840\), and \(N - 833 = 7\). The side lengths are \(\sqrt{x}\), \(\sqrt{x+7}\), and \(\sqrt{10-x}\). For these to form a non-degenerate triangle, the triangle inequalities must hold strictly. Solving these inequalities yields \(0.2 < x < 9\). The interval length is \(8.8\), and the total interval length is \(10\), so the probability is \(8.8/10 = 22/25\).

